comments.body:
@mheon yeah, sorry for the confusion on the reproducer. Similar to #8741 I'm trying to understand why my podman-managed containers suddenly stopped working. In this case I had been running CoreDNS via podman by publishing the UDP port to a specific interface, `-p 10.100.10.5:53:53/udp` but that has stopped working.

The reproducer I captured above doesn't capture the problem I'm seeing. I can launch one container with `-p 10.100.10.5:53:53/udp` and use socat to see "Hello World" on 10.100.10.5:53.

But my container that runs CoreDNS (via systemd) still doesn't seem to receive any traffic on this port. I'm not sure how to debug this further since (1) it used to work, and (2) there's nothing obviously wrong with UDP traffic since nc/socat work OK when I run them manually.
